==English==

===Etymology===
First attested [[w:1812|1812]]. Common [[folklore]] holds that his origins come from the men of an army base in [[Troy]], [[New York]], who would receive [[barrel]]s of meat stamped with the initials U.S. The soldiers [[jokingly]] referred to it as the initials of the meat [[supplier]], '''Uncle Samuel Wilson'''.

